AB  - An interpretable machine learning framework for predicting in-hospital mortality in sepsis patients upon ICU admission. Using retrospective data from a tertiary university hospital (January 2019 to June 2024), the study addressed class imbalance and missing data through synthetic oversampling and imputation. A hybrid approach combined ensemble algorithms with deep learning, optimized via the Red Piranha algorithm. The model achieved an AUC of 0.96, a Brier score of 0.118, and a recall of 81%, demonstrating superior predictive performance over conventional scoring systems.
